---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const meta = {
  title: 'Squarespace Review 2025: Design-First Website Builder',
  description: 'Squarespace review ($16-49/month): Design-first website builder with polished templates. Easy for beginners. Strong e-commerce. All-in-one hosting included. Best for small businesses, portfolios, online stores. Not for custom functionality. Higher cost than some alternatives.',
  image: '/og-image.svg',
  keywords: ['Squarespace review', 'website builder', 'no-code platform', 'Squarespace pricing', 'Squarespace e-commerce'],
};
---

<Layout {...meta}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-[#E04F5F]/5 to-[#FF4D8D]/5 py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <p class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-black text-[#E04F5F] mb-4 tracking-[0.3em] uppercase">
        Website Builder Review · 2025
      </p>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black mb-6 leading-tight">
        Squarespace Review
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 mb-8">
        Squarespace is the website builder for people who want beautiful results without learning to code. The templates are consistently excellent. The editor is intuitive. The e-commerce is surprisingly capable. Everything is included - hosting, security, backups, domains. You pay more than some alternatives, but you get a polished product without the hassle. Squarespace is the default choice for small businesses, portfolios, and online stores who care about aesthetics.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-white bg-opacity-50 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
          Quick verdict: Squarespace is the easiest way to create a professional-looking website. Choose it if you want beautiful templates, easy editing, and don't mind paying. Choose alternatives if you need maximum customization or want the cheapest option.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quick Summary -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      At a Glance
    </h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">What Squarespace Does Well</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Beautiful templates out of the box</li>
          <li>• Easy drag-and-drop editor</li>
          <li>• Built-in e-commerce features</li>
          <li>• All-in-one hosting included</li>
          <li>• Reliable performance and uptime</li>
          <li>• 24/7 customer support</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Where Squarespace Struggles</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Template constraints limit creativity</li>
          <li>• Expensive compared to some alternatives</li>
          <li>• Limited third-party integrations</li>
          <li>• No app marketplace like competitors</li>
          <li>• Migration can be difficult</li>
          <li>• Less control for advanced users</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Deep Dive -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What Makes Squarespace Different
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-pink-50 border-2 border-pink-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Design-First Philosophy</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Squarespace was built by designers. It shows.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Every template looks professional. Typography, spacing, color schemes - all polished. You can't make a bad-looking site. Competitors have more templates but inconsistent quality. Squarespace has fewer templates but they're all excellent.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-pink-50 border-2 border-pink-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">True All-in-One Platform</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Hosting, security, backups, domains - everything included.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> You don't think about technical details. Squarespace handles hosting, SSL certificates, security updates, backups. You just build your site. WordPress requires plugins and technical knowledge. Squarespace just works.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-pink-50 border-2 border-pink-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Surprisingly Strong E-commerce</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Built-in online store features that rival dedicated platforms.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Abandoned cart recovery, product options, inventory management, tax calculation - features that other website builders charge extra for. Squarespace e-commerce is mature enough for serious online stores.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-pink-50 border-2 border-pink-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Beginner-Friendly Editor</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Intuitive interface with gentle learning curve.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> If you've never built a website, Squarespace is the friendliest start. Pick a template, swap content, adjust fonts and colors, publish. Most people go from zero to live site in a weekend.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-pink-50 border-2 border-pink-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Reliable Performance</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Fast loading times and excellent uptime.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Your site loads fast automatically. Squarespace optimizes images, caching, and serving. No technical knowledge required. Competitors let you accidentally slow down your site. Squarespace prevents this.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Pricing Explained
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-pink-50 border-2 border-pink-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Personal - $16/month annually ($23 monthly)</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">For individuals and personal projects.</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• One website</li>
          <li>• 20 pages</li>
          <li>• Built-in marketing tools</li>
          <li>• Templates and styles</li>
          <li>• 24/7 customer support</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> Portfolios, resumes, personal blogs, hobby sites.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-pink-50 border-2 border-pink-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Business - $23/month annually ($33 monthly)</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">For small businesses and professionals.</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Everything in Personal, plus:</li>
          <li>• Unlimited pages</li>
          <li>• Marketing features and integrations</li>
          <li>• Advanced analytics</li>
          <li>• Professional email from Google</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> Small businesses, consultants, agencies, restaurants.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-pink-50 border-2 border-pink-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Commerce Basic - $27/month annually ($36 monthly)</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">For online stores selling physical or digital products.</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Everything in Business, plus:</li>
          <li>• Online store functionality</li>
          <li>• Product management</li>
          <li>• Inventory and order management</li>
          <li>• Commerce analytics</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> Small online stores, businesses with 10-100 products.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-pink-50 border-2 border-pink-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Commerce Advanced - $49/month annually ($65 monthly)</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">For growing online stores.</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Everything in Commerce Basic, plus:</li>
          <li>• Abandoned cart recovery</li>
          <li>• Advanced shipping and discounts</li>
          <li>• Subscriptions and product options</li>
          <li>• Commerce APIs</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> Serious online stores with 100+ products.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who It's For -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Who Should Use Squarespace
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ Perfect For</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Beginners:</strong> Never built a website before</li>
          <li>• <strong>Small businesses:</strong> Restaurants, consultants, agencies, local businesses</li>
          <li>• <strong>Portfolios:</strong> Designers, photographers, artists, architects</li>
          <li>• <strong>Online stores:</strong> Small to medium e-commerce (up to ~500 products)</li>
          <li>• <strong>People who care about aesthetics:</strong> Want professional-looking site without hiring a designer</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">❌ Not For</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Advanced users:</strong> Want full control over every element</li>
          <li>• <strong>Custom functionality:</strong> Need features beyond what Squarespace offers</li>
          <li>• <strong>Large e-commerce:</strong> 1000+ products (Shopify is better)</li>
          <li>• <strong>Budget-conscious:</strong> Want cheapest option (WordPress is cheaper long-term)</li>
          <li>• <strong>Developers:</strong> Prefer coding over visual builders</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Alternatives -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Squarespace Alternatives
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-gray-50 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Wix - $17-159/month</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Maximum flexibility with drag-and-drop editor.</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Pros:</strong> More design freedom, huge template variety, massive app market</li>
          <li>• <strong>Cons:</strong> More complex learning curve, can create messy designs</li>
          <li>• <strong>Best for:</strong> People who want maximum control and customization</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Framer - $5-40/month</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Modern visual builder with Figma integration.</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Pros:</strong> Faster workflow, Figma import, better performance, cheaper</li>
          <li>• <strong>Cons:</strong> Newer platform, less mature, e-commerce is basic</li>
          <li>• <strong>Best for:</strong> Designers, portfolios, marketing sites</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Webflow - $16-212/month</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Powerful no-code for designers who want control.</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Pros:</strong> Pixel-perfect control, clean code export, powerful CMS</li>
          <li>• <strong>Cons:</strong> Steep learning curve (2-4 weeks), e-commerce is basic</li>
          <li>• <strong>Best for:</strong> Designers who want visual control without coding</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">WordPress - Free (self-hosted)</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Open-source with unlimited plugins.</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Pros:</strong> Unlimited flexibility, cheaper long-term, huge ecosystem</li>
          <li>• <strong>Cons:</strong> Maintenance burden, plugin conflicts, learning required</li>
          <li>• <strong>Best for:</strong> Complex functionality, content sites, large e-commerce</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bottom Line -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <div class="bg-white bg-opacity-50 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded-xl p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-black mb-6">Bottom Line</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">Squarespace is the easiest path to a professional-looking website. The templates are beautiful. The editor is intuitive. The features are powerful. Everything just works. You pay more than some alternatives, but you save time and frustration. For small businesses, portfolios, and online stores who care about aesthetics, Squarespace is the default choice.</p>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6"><strong>Choose Squarespace if:</strong></p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <li>• You want beautiful results with minimal effort</li>
        <li>• You're a beginner or want an easy experience</li>
        <li>• You're building a small business site or portfolio</li>
        <li>• You need e-commerce but don't want a separate platform</li>
        <li>• You value reliability over maximum customization</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6"><strong>Choose alternatives if:</strong></p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <li>• Wix: You want maximum design control</li>
        <li>• Framer: You're a designer who uses Figma</li>
        <li>• Webflow: You want pixel-perfect control and are willing to learn</li>
        <li>• WordPress: You need unlimited plugins or cheapest long-term option</li>
        <li>• Shopify: E-commerce is your primary focus (1000+ products)</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">Squarespace isn't the cheapest. It's not the most flexible. But it's the most reliable path to a beautiful website. For most people, that's what matters. You don't want to become a website expert. You want a professional online presence without the headache. Squarespace delivers exactly that. The templates are gorgeous. The editor is friendly. The support is responsive. You'll go from zero to live site in a weekend. That's worth the subscription cost for many people.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-6 text-gray-900">
      Related Reviews
    </h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <a href="/wix-vs-squarespace" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Wix vs Squarespace</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Flexibility vs design</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/framer-vs-squarespace" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Framer vs Squarespace</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Modern vs established</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
